description.narrative: The proposed Project aims at supporting the Government of Argentina to consolidate, strengthen, and increase the coverage of a lifelong learning and competency-based training system for disadvantaged adults 18 years or older with the objectives for those who participate to: (i) enhance employability (for unemployed); and (ii) improve career opportunities (for employed).

condition.narrative: Within 12 months after project effectiveness, the Minitr of labor would have carried out a systems audit of the MIS

title.narrative: Within a year, no less than 25 percent of certified adults obtaining registererd employment or higher salary.

comment.narrative: Baseline is 0 because certification was minimal before start of project and employment outcomes are not measured until 1 yearaftercertification.

title.narrative: Within a year, no less than 50 percent of adults receiving basic education certificates continuing training or education, obtainingregistered employment or higher salary

comment.narrative: Baseline is 0 because detailed information on certified adults was limited.
Lag reflects serious problems in receiving information from provinces. Ministry taking remedial actions to collect informationfrom schools.

title.narrative: Award of 100,000 secondary or primary education certificates to out-of-school adults.

comment.narrative: Baseline is 0 because no information was collected at the individual level of the certification results of adults.
Figure reflects problems in reporting of results by provinces.

title.narrative: No less than 50 percent of those in internships, employed within 12 months after participation

comment.narrative: Baseline is 0 because program did not exist prior to the project
Low number reflects mainly low number of internships so far. May need to supplement with other information on outcomes for thosenot participating in internships.
Special efforts are needed to increase the number of internships being identified by the Ministry of Labor as well as theemployment offices.

title.narrative: Certification of 70,000 workers according to competency-based occupational standards
Participation of 250,000 workers in competency-based training courses
300 competency-based occupational standards registered by sector groups

comment.narrative: Ministry expects end-of-project target to be reached since certification process has been streamlined.
